1
00:00:01,550 --> 00:00:02,980
Watanabe!

2
00:00:03,560 --> 00:00:05,980
I have class duties today, so I'm gonna get going.

3
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:08,480
Is this all the recycling we have to put out today?

4
00:00:09,040 --> 00:00:10,990
That's all we have today.

5
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:12,510
Wait.

6
00:00:12,510 --> 00:00:14,050
Your necktie is crooked.

7
00:00:14,050 --> 00:00:15,240
Oh, thanks.

8
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,240
I'm just a background guy with nothing going for me,

9
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:20,240
and yet...

10
00:00:20,240 --> 00:00:21,750
Crouch down a little.

11
00:00:21,750 --> 00:00:24,250
The class gyaru ended up being my mock wife.

12
00:00:24,250 --> 00:00:27,740
She really is cute. It's no wonder she's popular.

13
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:33,280
Staring at my chest like that all the time is creepy as hell.

14
00:00:29,800 --> 00:00:36,300
SQUEEEEEEEEZE

15
00:00:33,280 --> 00:00:36,300
I wasn't! Y-You've got it all wrong!

16
00:00:42,840 --> 00:00:45,310
Take care out there, Jiro.

17
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:47,390
Sometimes, I fall under a delusion...

18
00:00:47,390 --> 00:00:49,820
What if I really was married to Watanabe?

19
00:00:52,320 --> 00:00:54,200
And we're done!

20
00:00:54,200 --> 00:00:56,760
Don't forget to take out the recycling!

21
00:00:58,600 --> 00:01:01,390
Guess I'll give it everything I've got again today.

22
00:01:02,870 --> 00:01:08,730
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

23
00:01:17,950 --> 00:01:19,850
It's criminal to be so shy

24
00:01:19,850 --> 00:01:23,700
Intelligence and wild fancies, tick tock, just pick a mood

25
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,000
A drizzle from a patch of blue sky

26
00:01:27,030 --> 00:01:29,290
No less than supreme

27
00:01:29,290 --> 00:01:32,710
A maiden's heart zigzags, cute and invincible

28
00:01:33,590 --> 00:01:35,320
The wild ringing of bells

29
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:42,430
What percentage does "like" have to hit before you can call it "love"?

30
00:01:43,180 --> 00:01:46,100
Hold me so tightly that I fall asleep

31
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:51,650
A daydream that seems like fiction

32
00:01:51,650 --> 00:01:54,690
Give me a kiss that breaks the expectant silence of the play

33
00:01:54,690 --> 00:01:57,110
Give that indecision a tight embrace, too

34
00:01:57,430 --> 00:01:59,740
My heart hurts and hurts,

35
00:01:59,740 --> 00:02:04,620
racing unpredictably with joy and excitement

36
00:02:04,620 --> 00:02:08,110
It's TRUE FOOL LOVE! Hold me tight!

37
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:10,430
Be brave, my darling

38
00:02:10,430 --> 00:02:13,010
It won't all be happy and fun

39
00:02:13,010 --> 00:02:15,030
It's all up to us

40
00:02:15,030 --> 00:02:17,240
ONCE MORE SMILE, TWICE MORE CHIME

41
00:02:17,240 --> 00:02:20,890
Please look my way, darling

42
00:02:21,910 --> 00:02:29,990
Please notice my pure love for you

43
00:02:35,490 --> 00:02:37,860
Oh, Jiro-kun.

44
00:02:37,860 --> 00:02:39,010
Good morning!

45
00:02:39,010 --> 00:02:40,800
Hey, you're here early.

46
00:02:40,800 --> 00:02:42,260
I've got class duties today.

47
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:44,680
Huh? Wasn't it me and Hamano today?

48
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,520
Oh, crap! Did I get the days mixed up?

49
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:53,270
Class Duties

50
00:02:46,980 --> 00:02:50,040
Mei-chan has a club leaders' meeting after school today,

51
00:02:50,040 --> 00:02:52,310
so she asked me to take over for her.

52
00:02:52,310 --> 00:02:53,270
For real?

53
00:02:54,050 --> 00:02:57,780
We haven't done class duties together since middle school, huh?

54
00:02:57,780 --> 00:02:59,900
Th-That's right.

55
00:03:00,200 --> 00:03:03,910
This is crazy! It can't be real! I'm insanely lucky today!

56
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:06,040
Class Duties

57
00:03:03,910 --> 00:03:08,430
Sakurazaka Yakuin

58
00:03:08,430 --> 00:03:11,420
Thanks, Mei-chan.

59
00:03:11,420 --> 00:03:15,040
So, your plan to jump him first thing in the morning failed?

60
00:03:16,800 --> 00:03:19,480
I had no such plan!

61
00:03:19,480 --> 00:03:20,550
Sorry.

62
00:03:21,930 --> 00:03:25,280
But why not just tell him how you feel? We're talking about Yakuin here.

63
00:03:25,280 --> 00:03:27,940
I know it'd work out for you. No problem.

64
00:03:27,940 --> 00:03:31,810
Jiro-kun... doesn't think of me that way.

65
00:03:31,810 --> 00:03:35,190
Uh, yeah, no matter how you look at it, he definitely does.

66
00:03:35,190 --> 00:03:38,520
I've never seen him even talking with another girl.

67
00:03:38,520 --> 00:03:39,780
That's just it.

68
00:03:41,430 --> 00:03:44,360
Up until now, it's only been me.

69
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:47,080
He didn't know any other girls.

70
00:03:48,330 --> 00:03:51,840
Well, since I've given you this chance by swapping class duties with you,

71
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:53,580
you should take action!

72
00:03:54,050 --> 00:03:57,460
If you want to make him notice you, you'll have to at least kiss him.

73
00:03:57,460 --> 00:03:58,160
Ki—

74
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:02,270
If you keep dragging your heels, that mock wife of his might jump him instead.

75
00:04:03,240 --> 00:04:06,340
Kidding! I'm just joking.

76
00:04:07,200 --> 00:04:08,870
Be more confident in yourself.

77
00:04:08,870 --> 00:04:11,340
You're a great girl.

78
00:04:12,370 --> 00:04:13,960
You feel better now, right?

79
00:04:14,440 --> 00:04:15,260
Yeah.

80
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:19,410
Sorry.

81
00:04:19,410 --> 00:04:20,540
Got a cold?

82
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:22,090
Bet someone's talking about you.

83
00:04:22,090 --> 00:04:23,360
Cut it out.

84
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,840
You sure are popular.

85
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:26,210
Speaking of rumors,

86
00:04:26,210 --> 00:04:29,370
apparently about ten pairs have started dating now.

87
00:04:29,370 --> 00:04:32,760
What? So the "practical magic" really does exist.

88
00:04:32,760 --> 00:04:34,810
Well, when you spend every day together...

89
00:04:34,810 --> 00:04:37,940
They're just getting caught up in the mood of it, that's all.

90
00:04:43,790 --> 00:04:46,010
Huh? What is it?

91
00:04:46,400 --> 00:04:51,360
Akari-san, you've been watching Yakuin a lot lately, haven't you?

92
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,000
What? What are you talking about?

93
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:56,480
I'll be cheering you on no matter who you love,

94
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:59,020
but I might have a hard time with Virgin-kun.

95
00:04:59,020 --> 00:04:59,720
Wha—

96
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:04,420
Akari's so pure. In a way, someone of his type would be sort of reassuring.

97
00:05:04,420 --> 00:05:06,980
Better than getting snagged by some creep.

98
00:05:06,980 --> 00:05:09,490
What? That's not happening.

99
00:05:09,490 --> 00:05:12,290
It's obvious that Minami-kun is the peak of humanity.

100
00:05:12,290 --> 00:05:15,870
So she's still stricken with the Minami bug, huh?

101
00:05:15,870 --> 00:05:18,490
Well, I guess we'll just leave it at that.

102
00:05:18,490 --> 00:05:19,790
I'm telling you...

103
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,300
Japanese History, Complete Collection World Atlas Collection North America World Atlas Collection South America World Atlas Collection Asia European Culture

104
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:26,360
Is that the last of it?

105
00:05:26,360 --> 00:05:28,080
Yeah, it is.

106
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:30,580
I'm sorry to have made you carry so much.

107
00:05:30,580 --> 00:05:32,560
Not a problem! It's totally fine!

108
00:05:32,890 --> 00:05:34,680
Thanks, Jiro-kun.

109
00:05:35,040 --> 00:05:35,960
Sure.

110
00:05:37,580 --> 00:05:39,920
So all that's left is cleaning the blackboard, right?

111
00:05:39,920 --> 00:05:40,620
Yeah.

112
00:05:40,620 --> 00:05:44,460
This brought back memories, huh? Like being back in middle school.

113
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:46,320
Yeah.

114
00:05:49,320 --> 00:05:51,480
Don't just say "yeah" and stop!

115
00:05:51,480 --> 00:05:53,200
That ended the conversation!

116
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:56,190
Think of something to talk about... Something...

117
00:05:58,550 --> 00:06:00,760
I can't think of anything...

118
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:05,720
Jiro-kun, since we're talking about it, do you remember Hatae-sensei?

119
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,560
The science teacher.

120
00:06:06,560 --> 00:06:09,340
Huh? Oh, the one with the crazy clothes?

121
00:06:09,690 --> 00:06:13,040
Yeah, him! I ran into him at the grocery store the other day.

122
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:16,100
He was wearing a bright red aloha shirt. I recognized him right away!

123
00:06:16,100 --> 00:06:18,960
For real? That brings back memories.

124
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:20,600
I guess he hasn't changed, then.

125
00:06:24,610 --> 00:06:27,610
Jiro Today Where are you? I'm gonna go shopping. Come with me Why hasn't he read my message yet?

126
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:31,340
This makes it seem like I really want to go shopping together.

127
00:06:31,340 --> 00:06:32,120
Jeez...

128
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:36,080
Oh, that's right! He's got class duties!

129
00:06:36,080 --> 00:06:37,000
Jir—

130
00:06:45,290 --> 00:06:47,740
Why am I hiding?

131
00:07:02,010 --> 00:07:02,940
Sorry!

132
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:18,750
Jiro-kun, close your eyes and lean down a little.

133
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:22,860
Huh? Is this a dream?

134
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,960
Close my eyes and lean down a little?

135
00:07:27,820 --> 00:07:29,970
What's going on?!

136
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:35,970
Huh?

137
00:07:36,380 --> 00:07:38,970
You had chalk dust on you.

138
00:07:38,970 --> 00:07:40,060
Thanks!

139
00:07:40,060 --> 00:07:42,980
No worries. I'll go beat these, okay?

140
00:07:42,980 --> 00:07:44,260
That was a close one!

141
00:07:44,260 --> 00:07:45,700
And holy crap, I'm creepy!

142
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:46,980
So very not okay!

143
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:48,360
Class Duties Yakuin

144
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:52,990
Sakurazaka

145
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:52,990
Even after we were together for a whole day, this is where we are.

146
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,670
I knew I wouldn't be able to do it!

147
00:07:59,670 --> 00:08:01,350
I'm sorry, Mei-chan!

148
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:04,000
Sakurazaka

149
00:08:05,910 --> 00:08:08,460
So nothing happened in the end...

150
00:08:09,930 --> 00:08:13,140
But if I'd confessed my feelings back in middle school and been turned down,

151
00:08:13,140 --> 00:08:16,010
we wouldn't have been able to talk today like we did.

152
00:08:16,450 --> 00:08:18,380
I'm so dull and boring.

153
00:08:18,380 --> 00:08:20,720
If she's got a memory of me tucked away somewhere,

154
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:22,280
I should count myself lucky!

155
00:08:24,530 --> 00:08:26,440
What're you being all melancholy about?

156
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:37,680
I made too much hot milk.

157
00:08:38,160 --> 00:08:39,080
Want some?

158
00:08:39,080 --> 00:08:42,340
Oh, I'll have some, then. Thanks.

159
00:08:42,340 --> 00:08:44,010
You seem down.

160
00:08:44,920 --> 00:08:46,080
Not really.

161
00:08:46,420 --> 00:08:48,700
Did things go well with Sakurazaka-san?

162
00:08:50,010 --> 00:08:52,090
Oh, you know... Well enough.

163
00:08:52,090 --> 00:08:54,440
You suck at lying, you know that?

164
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:57,100
Shut up! If you know, then don't ask!

165
00:08:57,100 --> 00:08:59,600
Poor thing. There, there.

166
00:08:58,540 --> 00:08:59,600
Stop making it worse!

167
00:09:01,170 --> 00:09:03,360
The night sky is so damn bright.

168
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:08,530
You're right! You can see more stars than you'd expect!

169
00:09:08,530 --> 00:09:10,240
Right? It's pretty, huh?

170
00:09:10,240 --> 00:09:11,230
Wow!

171
00:09:12,070 --> 00:09:17,240
I bet the stars would look even prettier if I was with Minami-kun.

172
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:20,240
Well, sorry it's just boring old me.

173
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:24,750
Though I'm sure the stars would feel honored to have Tenjin-kun looking at them.

174
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,630
Hey, try calling me by my first name.

175
00:09:31,140 --> 00:09:32,650
That's hot!

176
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:35,060
Well, come on. "A-ka-ri"!

177
00:09:35,060 --> 00:09:36,600
Where'd this even come from?

178
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:38,280
I don't want to!

179
00:09:39,320 --> 00:09:42,960
So you call Sakurazaka-san "Shiori," but you call your wife by her last name?

180
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:45,400
That's just because...

181
00:09:45,400 --> 00:09:48,900
Sh-Shiori is... you know. It's just different.

182
00:09:49,150 --> 00:09:51,780
You're embarrassed to call a girl by her first name!

183
00:09:51,780 --> 00:09:54,750
That's our virgin for you! Number 1 in Japan!

184
00:09:55,840 --> 00:09:57,900
I'm not falling for that.

185
00:09:58,250 --> 00:09:59,250
Boo.

186
00:10:00,910 --> 00:10:02,660
But I guess it's fine.

187
00:10:02,660 --> 00:10:04,410
I really like my name, you know?

188
00:10:04,410 --> 00:10:07,770
I like how it means "light" and is written using the character for "star."

189
00:10:07,770 --> 00:10:12,420
I don't really know why, but sometimes I lose confidence in myself, you know?

190
00:10:12,420 --> 00:10:15,970
At a time like that, if you happened to be by my side,

191
00:10:15,970 --> 00:10:18,030
and called me by my name...

192
00:10:18,030 --> 00:10:20,560
I thought it might feel comforting, that's all.

193
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:23,930
So practice it before that time comes, okay?

194
00:10:28,730 --> 00:10:29,940
Aka...ri.

195
00:10:31,940 --> 00:10:35,830
It's just... I mean, my name's so plain.

196
00:10:35,830 --> 00:10:38,840
If I had a cool name like that, I'd never live up to it.

197
00:10:38,840 --> 00:10:40,950
But... yours is nice.

198
00:10:41,250 --> 00:10:44,260
I think the name "Akari" suits you.

199
00:10:47,950 --> 00:10:51,960
I'm sorry, Watanabe-san. Let's just pretend that never happened.

200
00:10:53,630 --> 00:10:54,540
No.

201
00:10:55,610 --> 00:10:56,190
Huh?

202
00:11:01,740 --> 00:11:02,970
Again.

203
00:11:04,890 --> 00:11:05,970
And besides!

204
00:11:05,970 --> 00:11:10,100
Me calling you "Jiro" while you use my last name is sort of irritating!

205
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:11,850
What do you mean, "irritating"?

206
00:11:11,850 --> 00:11:14,110
It's like I'm the only one in love here!

207
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:16,110
That's a bizarre reason!

208
00:11:18,330 --> 00:11:19,110
Huh?

209
00:11:21,040 --> 00:11:22,020
In love?

210
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:27,570
It's not... It's not like that.

211
00:11:27,570 --> 00:11:30,100
It was hypothetical... f-for the practical.

212
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:35,880
No, um... I'm sorry, too. I sort of jumped to conclusions.

213
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:39,880
I-I've just never had anyone say anything like that to me before.

214
00:11:39,880 --> 00:11:41,630
G-G-Goodnight!

215
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:43,290
G-Goodnight.

216
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:51,890
She has Tenjin! There's no way she meant it like that!

217
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,900
Stop reacting like that, you idiot.

218
00:11:57,380 --> 00:11:59,990
God, I hate this!

219
00:12:02,220 --> 00:12:03,560
What do I do?

220
00:12:04,180 --> 00:12:05,910
I'm so confused.

221
00:12:07,480 --> 00:12:09,450
Around this same time every year,

222
00:12:09,450 --> 00:12:13,210
with the marriage practical underway, we see a drop in concentration,

223
00:12:13,210 --> 00:12:14,960
but it's particularly pronounced this year.

224
00:12:14,960 --> 00:12:18,960
Which is why we will immediately begin having special tests.

225
00:12:19,340 --> 00:12:20,960
Just like the regularly scheduled tests,

226
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,970
any students who fail will take supplementary lessons.

227
00:12:22,970 --> 00:12:26,380
Seriously?! I'm a serial offender when it comes to failing!

228
00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:28,010
But this time, the scores of the married pairs in the practical will be combined,

229
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:30,110
And depending on your pairing, you could get a major handicap.

230
00:12:28,010 --> 00:12:30,110
and supplementary lessons will be taken together, as well.

231
00:12:30,110 --> 00:12:31,730
My wife's gonna kill me. What?! That's just inane!

232
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:35,160
What? It's sold out? Talk about a letdown.

233
00:12:32,810 --> 00:12:38,000
The test will be next weekend, and married pairs must take supplementary lessons together.

234
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:38,000
Why'd they even list it? That's so misleading.

235
00:12:36,810 --> 00:12:38,000
Hang on.

236
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,900
Depending on the subject, I'm below average!

237
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:41,990
Make the most of your time after school by assisting each other.

238
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:41,990
This is so not funny!

239
00:12:42,280 --> 00:12:45,950
It goes without saying that Shiori and Tenjin will get high scores.

240
00:12:45,950 --> 00:12:48,480
If I get failing grades...

241
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,340
Hey.

242
00:12:50,960 --> 00:12:52,480
Ass in the air, bitch.

243
00:12:52,480 --> 00:12:53,500
She's gonna kill me!

244
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:56,790
Karaoke? Yeah, I'll go! Yay!

245
00:12:56,670 --> 00:12:57,500
Wait.

246
00:12:56,790 --> 00:12:59,330
We're gonna sing until we're hoarse!

247
00:12:57,840 --> 00:13:00,500
Is Watanabe good at academics?

248
00:13:00,970 --> 00:13:05,010
Until we're hoarse? Just how much stress have you built up, exactly? She comes to class, but she goes to hang out with friends every day.

249
00:13:05,460 --> 00:13:07,250
She couldn't be...

250
00:13:07,250 --> 00:13:09,510
Hey, it's Jiro!

251
00:13:09,510 --> 00:13:13,020
Buy us some fabric softener. The one with the green flowers.

252
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:17,600
Sure... H-Hey, I wanna talk later about the academic performance tes—

253
00:13:17,600 --> 00:13:18,680
Oh, sorry!

254
00:13:18,680 --> 00:13:20,710
I got invited out to karaoke today.

255
00:13:20,710 --> 00:13:23,530
Apparently, we'll be singing with some guys from some boys' school.

256
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:25,950
What? Does that bother you? Tee-hee!

257
00:13:25,950 --> 00:13:27,280
Are you jealous?

258
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,540
No!

259
00:13:28,540 --> 00:13:30,530
You're fine for the test, then?

260
00:13:31,980 --> 00:13:33,540
Totally fine!

261
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:36,480
It'll be fine. Everything'll work out somehow.

262
00:13:36,480 --> 00:13:38,010
"Somehow"?

263
00:13:38,010 --> 00:13:41,930
Aren't there subjects you're not as good at, or areas you don't understand?

264
00:13:43,550 --> 00:13:45,640
Areas I don't understand, huh?

265
00:13:46,540 --> 00:13:49,470
Hmm... What were the areas again?

266
00:13:50,300 --> 00:13:52,930
Watanabe, look me in the eye and say that to me.

267
00:13:53,270 --> 00:13:56,440
I-If I start working hard tomorrow...

268
00:13:56,440 --> 00:13:58,290
it'll be fine.

269
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,280
Let's head home.

270
00:14:00,280 --> 00:14:02,440
I can't! They asked for me.

271
00:14:03,360 --> 00:14:06,250
Look, what if you have to take supplementary lessons?

272
00:14:06,250 --> 00:14:08,200
You'll end up even farther from Tenjin!

273
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,480
Yeah, but...

274
00:14:09,480 --> 00:14:11,100
But nothing!

275
00:14:11,100 --> 00:14:12,960
You can hang out with your friends anytime!

276
00:14:12,960 --> 00:14:14,610
It's not like that!

277
00:14:14,610 --> 00:14:17,090
It's the guys who asked for me, not my friends.

278
00:14:17,090 --> 00:14:18,460
That's harder to turn down.

279
00:14:18,780 --> 00:14:21,210
Guys? Well, I'm asking for you here, too.

280
00:14:22,280 --> 00:14:24,060
Let's go, Watanabe.

281
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:30,370
All right! I get it already, okay?

282
00:14:31,130 --> 00:14:32,720
This sucks.

283
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,220
You're way too desperate about this.

284
00:14:35,120 --> 00:14:37,720
Just because Sakurazaka-san's involved...

285
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:42,050
Oh, I get it! I just have to go like this!

286
00:14:42,050 --> 00:14:44,950
All that's left is applying it in practice.

287
00:14:44,950 --> 00:14:46,230
You're amazing, Shiori.

288
00:14:46,630 --> 00:14:48,170
You make it so easy to understand!

289
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:51,630
Man, these special tests...

290
00:14:51,630 --> 00:14:54,670
You're probably feeling good with Tenjin as your partner,

291
00:14:54,670 --> 00:14:57,480
but there were a bunch of pairs who were panicking about them.

292
00:14:57,480 --> 00:15:00,750
But you pick things up quickly, so you'll be fine!

293
00:15:01,230 --> 00:15:04,130
I'm confident when it comes to sports,

294
00:15:04,130 --> 00:15:06,190
but with academics, not so much.

295
00:15:07,570 --> 00:15:10,010
But I feel like I might just manage this. Thanks!

296
00:15:10,010 --> 00:15:11,440
I'm glad.

297
00:15:11,440 --> 00:15:15,390
As thanks, I'll give you a lecture on how to plan for things of that other type.

298
00:15:15,390 --> 00:15:17,020
What other type?

299
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:19,380
The kissing type.

300
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:21,700
Mei-chan!

301
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:26,110
Man, I laughed so hard about what happened two days ago.

302
00:15:26,110 --> 00:15:27,000
Oh, come on!

303
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:30,260
Yakuin being the way Yakuin is, and you being the way you are...

304
00:15:30,260 --> 00:15:32,150
Stop talking about it!

305
00:15:40,020 --> 00:15:42,040
By the way, last time...

306
00:15:45,790 --> 00:15:47,920
I don't wanna do this anymore! I need a break!

307
00:15:47,920 --> 00:15:50,900
You've only solved a handful of problems, though.

308
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,490
This is bad.

309
00:15:53,490 --> 00:15:55,760
She picks things up fast when I teach her,

310
00:15:55,760 --> 00:15:59,430
but she just fundamentally hates studying.

311
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,850
Come on, let's just try for a little longer.

312
00:16:02,850 --> 00:16:07,440
I can help you a little with math, and we can tackle the rest together, okay?

313
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:09,140
Yeah?

314
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:12,470
For Sakurazaka-san's sake, right?

315
00:16:12,470 --> 00:16:14,540
Huh? Sorry, what did you say?

316
00:16:15,740 --> 00:16:17,730
Nothing.

317
00:16:34,590 --> 00:16:38,100
Hey, Jiro. Let's do something more fun than studying.

318
00:16:39,590 --> 00:16:41,140
What do you want to do?

319
00:16:41,140 --> 00:16:43,600
Whatever you want to do, I'll do it with you.

320
00:16:45,730 --> 00:16:46,600
Well?

321
00:16:47,490 --> 00:16:49,610
What shall we do?

322
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:59,690
S-Study! We're going to study!

323
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:03,180
Ugh. Study, study. My ears hurt.

324
00:17:03,180 --> 00:17:05,120
My plan failed.

325
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:06,150
Listen—

326
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:08,000
You're so dense.

327
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:10,560
What made you think a blatant strategy like that would work?

328
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,470
I swear...

329
00:17:13,720 --> 00:17:16,640
Hey, Watanabe. You did this right up to here.

330
00:17:16,640 --> 00:17:17,540
Really?! Yeah.

331
00:17:19,240 --> 00:17:21,700
Try solving it like you did the one before it.

332
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:25,680
Um, so... 2x is t, right?

333
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:27,590
So this comes first...

334
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:31,020
Oh, man! I think I get it!

335
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:36,820
It...

336
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:38,860
It's over!

337
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:40,330
You worked really hard!

338
00:17:40,680 --> 00:17:42,830
We made it further than I thought we would.

339
00:17:42,830 --> 00:17:45,500
I told you it wouldn't be a problem, didn't I?

340
00:17:46,220 --> 00:17:48,110
I might seriously be a genius.

341
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:49,580
Yeah. You might be right.

342
00:17:50,010 --> 00:17:52,470
She's the type that improves through obvious praise.

343
00:17:53,590 --> 00:17:56,820
Wh-What? I really do think that!

344
00:17:57,910 --> 00:18:00,100
Thanks, Jiro-sensei.

345
00:18:00,790 --> 00:18:02,100
Just kidding!

346
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:05,730
Your heart just started racing, didn't it?

347
00:18:05,730 --> 00:18:08,970
Guys seem to like that sort of thing. Why is that?

348
00:18:08,970 --> 00:18:10,460
How am I supposed to know?

349
00:18:10,460 --> 00:18:13,110
Come on. Let's get this cleaned up and have something to eat.

350
00:18:13,110 --> 00:18:15,970
Okay. Let's do that, Sensei.

351
00:18:17,020 --> 00:18:19,600
What is this? She's really pestering me a lot today.

352
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,120
So how about that one?

353
00:18:21,390 --> 00:18:23,060
Did that make your heart race?

354
00:18:23,060 --> 00:18:25,710
My heart did not race, then or now.

355
00:18:26,310 --> 00:18:28,120
Stop that! Come on, just clean up!

356
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:31,480
It's infuriating.

357
00:18:31,480 --> 00:18:33,920
You're just Jiro, but you're better at academics than me.

358
00:18:33,920 --> 00:18:36,630
At least get a little wound up. I feel like I'm losing here.

359
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:41,640
Get wound up? Look, this isn't about winning or losing—

360
00:18:42,270 --> 00:18:44,640
Huh?! Wait... H-Hey!

361
00:18:46,370 --> 00:18:48,140
Then how about this?

362
00:18:50,460 --> 00:18:51,760
Is your heart racing now?

363
00:18:53,270 --> 00:18:56,380
You're ignoring me again! That really pisses me off, you know!

364
00:18:56,380 --> 00:18:57,150
Remember!

365
00:18:57,540 --> 00:19:00,660
Remember that grotesque scene from the movie you saw yesterday!

366
00:19:03,070 --> 00:19:03,660
Wait!

367
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:06,610
You're always sneaking glances, right?

368
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:08,640
Go on. You can look.

369
00:19:13,820 --> 00:19:17,170
Shit! Not this again!

370
00:19:17,600 --> 00:19:20,680
Don't you dare lose, me!

371
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,060
Why...

372
00:19:31,690 --> 00:19:36,300
Damn it!

373
00:19:42,900 --> 00:19:47,700
Hey, the sound of your heart is pretty wild right now.

374
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:49,290
It's pounding so hard.

375
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,210
It is.

376
00:19:51,210 --> 00:19:54,050
Welp, you lose. Too bad for you.

377
00:20:01,240 --> 00:20:02,440
Wait, huh?

378
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:03,920
Hurry up and get off me.

379
00:20:05,780 --> 00:20:07,970
Why does your face look so serious?

380
00:20:08,760 --> 00:20:10,120
You can't, okay?

381
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:12,730
Wait... Your hand!

382
00:20:12,970 --> 00:20:14,270
Are you listening?

383
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:25,740
I said you can't!

384
00:20:35,260 --> 00:20:36,360
Jiro...

385
00:20:41,390 --> 00:20:42,260
Wait, Jiro!

386
00:20:42,260 --> 00:20:43,440
Your nose is bleeding!

387
00:20:49,980 --> 00:20:52,480
Oh my God! You're adorable!

388
00:20:52,480 --> 00:20:54,980
Damn it! Whose fault do you think this is?

389
00:20:54,980 --> 00:20:57,260
I really messed up!

390
00:20:57,260 --> 00:20:59,980
Thank you, nosebleed! You saved me.

391
00:21:00,840 --> 00:21:02,000
And anyway...

392
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,260
You've been acting weird all day.

393
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:08,880
Only because you're so desperate not to let Sakurazaka-san leave you behind.

394
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:09,490
What?

395
00:21:09,490 --> 00:21:13,500
You seemed so impatient and panicked. I just wanted to get you to take a breath.

396
00:21:14,450 --> 00:21:17,440
I'm not working this frantically just for myself.

397
00:21:18,180 --> 00:21:21,650
The sooner you can pair with Tenjin, the better, right?

398
00:21:21,650 --> 00:21:24,280
You're the one who always earns us points.

399
00:21:24,280 --> 00:21:26,260
I'm the one who holds us back.

400
00:21:26,840 --> 00:21:30,580
I mean, I'm sure you'd have done well no matter who you were paired with.

401
00:21:30,580 --> 00:21:33,140
I know how much you've helped me.

402
00:21:33,140 --> 00:21:38,780
I figured, with something like academics, I might be able to help you a bit, too,

403
00:21:38,780 --> 00:21:39,650
even at my level.

404
00:21:42,650 --> 00:21:45,720
Don't try to act cool with a tissue stuck up your nose.

405
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:48,910
Shut up! Would you just let that go already?!

406
00:21:48,910 --> 00:21:51,080
Don't say anything about it at school!

407
00:21:54,910 --> 00:21:58,250
Jiro If we keep going like this and reach A rank,

408
00:21:57,590 --> 00:22:00,120
and Jiro and I change our pairing...

409
00:22:00,520 --> 00:22:04,660
For the rest of my life, I'll never say "Welcome home" or "I'm back" to Jiro again.

410
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:08,630
And these clothes that smell of the same fabric softener

411
00:22:08,630 --> 00:22:11,100
will each take on different scents.

412
00:22:12,520 --> 00:22:14,660
But that's the right choice, isn't it?

413
00:22:15,310 --> 00:22:18,380
Because all of this is only study.

414
00:22:19,940 --> 00:22:23,920
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

415
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:28,350
I want to give love a try

416
00:22:28,350 --> 00:22:31,260
In this night when everything begins to overflow

417
00:22:31,260 --> 00:22:33,530
I match my stride to yours

418
00:22:33,530 --> 00:22:39,370
The clock hands stop, charmed by a fleeting curse

419
00:22:39,370 --> 00:22:43,940
The answers always slip away

420
00:22:43,940 --> 00:22:47,360
All I want is to do it over again

421
00:22:47,360 --> 00:22:52,760
If I did, would this unsettling gloom inside me disappear?

422
00:22:52,760 --> 00:22:57,060
I want to know where my heart is hiding

423
00:22:57,060 --> 00:23:01,840
One day this will end

424
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:04,640
I know that

425
00:23:04,640 --> 00:23:06,350
And I know the signs of discord

426
00:23:06,350 --> 00:23:08,400
Turn them inside out

427
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:10,000
Don't let them pile up

428
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:14,210
I don't want things to stay unfinished like this

429
00:23:14,210 --> 00:23:18,250
In this moment when I've deceived you on a cosmic scale

430
00:23:18,250 --> 00:23:22,680
I want to give love a try

431
00:23:22,680 --> 00:23:24,700
Everything begins to overflow

432
00:23:24,700 --> 00:23:27,890
On this day when we don't know how much time is left to us

433
00:23:27,890 --> 00:23:36,150
I want your thoughts to drift toward me fondly, again and again

434
00:23:50,390 --> 00:23:52,990
I got a lower score on our modern Japanese test than Akari did!

435
00:23:52,990 --> 00:23:57,990
Underlined 3 "What can be gained from finding something more enjoyable than studying? Imagine it and write about it."

436
00:23:53,420 --> 00:23:55,960
"Imagine something more fun than studying and write about it."

437
00:23:55,960 --> 00:23:57,990
What kind of question is that?!

438
00:23:57,990 --> 00:24:01,120
Hey, Jiro. Let's do something more fun than studying.

439
00:24:02,200 --> 00:24:04,280
Self-control!

440
00:24:04,280 --> 00:24:06,500
Nothing I came up with was appropriate to write!

441
00:24:06,500 --> 00:24:10,010
Next Time A Male Virgin, but No Female Virgin. Next time, "A Male Virgin, but No Female Virgin."

